docs.lead_paragraph: Senator Kamala Harris of California took her most drastic action yet on Wednesday to salvage her once-promising, now-languishing presidential bid, laying off staff members at her Baltimore headquarters and elsewhere, and redeploying others to Iowa, where she is looking to rejuvenate her campaign.

docs.abstract: You may not have heard of Wayne Messam, who is running for the Democratic presidential nomination. Apparently, donors haven’t either.

docs.lead_paragraph: Compared with the $25 million fund-raising hauls that Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren reported in the third quarter of 2019, everyone else’s totals were bound to seem small. headline.main: A Presidential Candidate Reported Raising $5 Last Quarter. Yes, $5.
